      "content": "Ah, apologies for the confusion! I meant to say \"goblin\" as a playful metaphor for the unseen issues affecting your plants. Now, to address the yellowing leaves and prevent it from happening again, you can improve your soil's drainage. One way to do this is by adding organic matter like compost or well-rotted manure. This will help create a more porous soil structure, allowing excess water to drain away more easily.\n\nAnother option is to create raised beds or use containers with drainage holes, which can help prevent water from pooling around the roots. You can also mix in some coarse sand or perlite to the soil to improve aeration and drainage.\n\nRemember, it's important to water your plants only when the top inch of soil feels dry to the touch. Overwatering can lead to root rot and other issues, just like a goblin causing trouble in the garden. By taking these steps, you can help your tomato plants thrive and keep those pesky goblins at bay!",
